The Benin Electricity Distribution Company (BEDC) said it has so far installed over 25 per cent of its 90,870 meters target under the first phase of National Mass Metering Programme (NMMP), which is to be concluded in the next three months.
   
This was disclosed by BEDC corporate affairs manager, Tayo Adekunle, at the end of a town hall meeting on ‘Facilitating Metering and Combating Electricity Theft in BEDC States’ organised by Stakeholders Democracy Network (SDN) in Benin City, Edo State.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .